ec\/speed 3.5<b>."},{"content":"Using a rolling pin, roll rested dough out very thinly (approx. 40 cm x 30 cm) and place on prepared baking tray."},{"content":"Spread cheese mixture over dough then arrange pear slices on top, overlapping slightly."},{"content":"Turn oven down to 210°C then bake for 20-25 minutes (210°C) until cooked."},{"content":"Remove from oven, sprinkle with walnuts and drizzle with honey. Serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Replace honey with cherry jam for a variation.","Will serve 6 large portions if served as a starter or lunch. If part of a sharing table or eaten at the same time as the cheese course, will serve 8."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","3h","6 portions"]}